  "body": "## Suggestion\r\n\r\nPassing parameters into truffle scripts. The documentation does not state if this is supported. If it is then documentation updates would be good, otherwise creating support would be desired.\r\nhttps://www.trufflesuite.com/docs/truffle/getting-started/writing-external-scripts\r\n\r\n## example use cases\r\n\r\nuseful for testing and demos.  I can run a \"populate data\" script and pass in how many widgets to create.  Helps with testing oracles.\r\n\r\ne.g. `truffle exec createWidget.js 4` would execute the script, passing in 4 as a param, which I can use in the script logic to loop and create 4 widgets, or create one with an ID of 4.\r\n",
